# Mneme (GitHub Copilot)

Copilot Chat (VS Code, JetBrains, GitHub.com) reads
`.github/copilot-instructions.md` as repo-level guidance. In VS Code,
Copilot can also call MCP tools (see `.vscode/mcp.json` ->
`servers.mneme`).

## Tool usage rules (MANDATORY)

**When MCP is available, call mneme MCP tools BEFORE Copilot's
built-in `#codebase`, `#file`, or `#search` references.** When MCP is
not available (Copilot Chat on GitHub.com), summarise the relevant
slice from mneme first using the CLI and paste it into the chat.

On every task:

1. `mneme.minimal_context(task="<description>")` — ~100 tokens.
2. Iterate with `mneme.query`, `mneme.impact`, `mneme.search`
   at `detail_level="minimal"`.
3. Open files only as directed. Budget: <= 5 calls + <= 800 tokens.

## Coding standards (Copilot)

- Use the symbols mneme returns. Do not invent function/module names.
- When suggesting an edit that changes a public signature, also surface
  the impact set from `mneme.impact(symbol=...)` in the explanation.

## Step ledger / drift / compaction

- Ledger: `~/.mneme/projects/<id>/steps.jsonl`.
- Address symbol/doc/test drift before declaring done.
- Re-prime via `mneme.minimal_context(...)` after any reset.
